<p>I have a sass map and variable</p>  <pre><code>$maps-color-brand: (   color: (     primary:     #111,     info:        #222,     success:     #333,     warning:     #444,     danger:      #555   ),   mix: (     light:       $fff,     dark:        $000   ),   percentage: (     light:       80%,     lighter:     20%,     dark:        80%,     darker:      60%   ) ); </code></pre>  <p>I want to mix them as shown below</p>  <pre><code>.primary {   color: #111; }  .primary-light {   color: mix(#111, #fff, 80%); }  .primary-darker {   color: mix(#111, #000, 60%); } </code></pre>  <p>I tried to mix them in the following manner</p>  <pre><code>@mixin color-mix($color, $mix, $percentage, $maps: $maps-color-brand) {   @each $key, $value in $maps {     $maps-color: map-get($value, color);     // i dont know how to get key and value inside $color, $mix and $percentage   } } </code></pre>  <p>But I get an error message. Any suitable method to mix it as desired?</p>